.\" Man page for lob-run
.TH LOB-RUN 1 "April 2026" "libobsh 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lob-run \- Execute a bash script directly from a Library coordinate
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lob-run
.I script.coord
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lob-run
fetches a bash script from the Library using its \fI.coord\fR file,
writes it to a temporary file, executes it, and removes the temporary
file afterward. The exit code of the script is preserved.
.PP
This command only works for bash scripts. For other file types,
use \fBlob-decode\fR.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B lob-run backup.coord
Runs the script referenced by \fIbackup.coord\fR.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lob-encode (1),
.BR lob-decode (1)
